description:
Overview

Stitch and his band of space pirates have designs on looting the wreckage of a crashed ore tug before the rightful owners can arrive to salvage the valuable cargo. The problem: a nest of Aliens has set up housekeeping near the wrecked tug. Stitch's solution: a cute little pig carrying a low-yield nuke wired to a remote detonator. Not since Babe has so much rested on the outcome of a porker's performance. How about a little bacon with your Alien eggs?

The crew of the commercial towing vessel Nostromo finds themselves being awoken from hyper-sleep prior to their arrival at Earth. The ship's computer has diverted them a mysterious planet, where it picked up an signal of unknown origin. After landing on the planet, the ship's captain, Dallas, it's navigator, Lambert, and the second-in-command Kane go to investigate, while the rest of the crew - Warrant Officer Ripley, Science Officer Ash, and the engineers Brett and Parker work on repairs and monitor Dallas's team's progress.

Dallas and company arrive at the source of the signal, and find a gigantic ship there. After investigating, they discover that the ship's crew is dead, and the hold is full of many strange eggs. When Kane goes to look closer, a creature (Facehugger) leaps from the egg, and wraps around his head, penetrating his helmet and implanting its ovipositor down his throat. Dallas and Lambert take Kane back to the ship, and against Ripley's objections, bring him aboard. The repairs are completed and the ship takes off. Once they were back in orbit and on their way, they try to remove the Facehugger from Kane and learn that it's clinging too tightly for them to pry it off, and it bleeds acid, so they can't cut it of without causing catastrophic damage to the ship. After they decide to put Kane into stasis, the facehugger releases Kane and dies. A little later Kane himself appears to recover. As they dine on their last meal before returning to hypersleep, the egg that the facehugger had implanted into Kane hatches, causing a young Alien to burst out of his chest (a Chestburster), killing Kane.

The crew proceeds to split into teams and search the ship for the Chestburster, using a motion detector designed by Ash. The team of Ripley, Brett, and Parker find the alien, only to make a horrible discovery, the Alien has grown dramatically larger, almost twice the size of a human. This discovery also comes at a terrible cost, as the alien kills Brett. The crew determines that the Alien is using the air ducts to move around, and the crew decides to use the air-ducts to force the Alien into the airlock and space it. Dallas volunteers to go into the air ducts with a motion detector and a flame thrower to track down the Alien. He too is killed by the Alien.

With Ripley in command now, she uses the ship's computer to try to figure out what to do about the Alien, and discover that the company they work for, Wayland-Yutani, was aware of the presence of the Alien on this planet, and had sent the ship there both to investigate, and to bring an Alien back. The ship's crew was considered expendable. As Ripley is reeling from this revelation, she makes another shocking discovery - Ash is an Android sent by the company to monitor the crew. Ash tries to kill her, but is stopped by Parker. The surviving crew decides to scuttle the ship and escape in the ship's escape pod. As Ripley sets up the self-destruct sequence and saves the ship's cat, Jonesy, Lambert and Parker are killed by the Alien. Ripley barely escapes before the ship is destroyed.

However, Ripley is not safe yet - the Alien is also on board the escape pod. Ripley dons a space suit and manages to knock the alien out into the vacuum of space. Upon achieving her final victory, Ripley enters the final log entry for the Nostromo and enters hyper-sleep with Jonesy.
name: GN

description:
A man and a woman, alone in a deserted shipyard, sometime in the future. They start playing their sexual games -- but suddenly things start taking a turn for the serious. Then the third member of the party shows up.... Magnificent art, kinky sensuality and a steady psychological gamesmanship distinguishes this erotic graphic novel!

----------

Night. Somewhere, somewhen. The man and the woman circle one another, like jungle cats. A weighted word here, a furtive touch there -- any moment now, one of them might go too far.

They have no past. They have no future. They have no names -- at least as far as this game is concerned. Because if their names were revealed, they would break the rules of the game.

Then that rule gets broken. And the other rules follow...

Internationally acclaimed German cartoonist Matthias Schultheiss (creator of the science fiction series Bell's Theorem and the futuristic super-hero comic Propellerman) brings his dark, brooding vision to the world of X-rated comics with Talk Dirty, a story of obsession and fulfillment.

In the end, the questions multiply: Which one is the predator? Which one is the victim? And what role will the third player take? Talk Dirty is a hardcore psychodrama that will leave the hardiest reader emotionally drained.

BONUS: This edition of Talk Dirty presents, for the first time anywhere, a selection of full-color pages from Schultheiss's earliest draft of the book.
name: Talk Dirty

description:
Cheeks The Toy Wonder makes his return in this darker than usual holiday special. Not only darker for a Christmas book, but dark for the Ambush Bug. Not only does Cheeks the Wonder Toy return, but he does so as a cannabalistic zombie. As the city notices stuffed animals and dolls everywhere are viciously attacked and eaten, it is the "Night of the Living Dolls". Also a whole lot of one page gas.

And a promise of a showdown between Ambush Bug and the Joker.
name: I Knew I Shoulda Taken That Left Toyn Back in Albakoyky

description:
The vintage classic from the pages of Heavy Metal, finally collected into one 88-page softcover volume of galactiporn, including the EROS-only final chapter! New gray tones by Thorne enrich the already-fabulous art!

----------

Lann makes Barbarella look like Cinderella! The vintage classic from the pages of Heavy Metal is finally collected into one volume of galactiporn, including the Eros-only final chapter! New gray tones by Thorne enrich the already-fabulous art, resulting in a lush, sensuous look far beyond any previous editions of this already wonderful work! It's a satirical and smutty sci-fi extravaganza filled with humor, adventure and orgies. Lann cruises the fleshpots of the alternate universe Neon-Six hot on the trail of lusty twin bombshells and goes deep undercover into the darkest shadows of the planet's porn industry ending up in a totally over-the-top production of Hitler Humps Hollywood, the world's first porn rap musical, starring Lann herself as Eva Braun! Also includes a photo spread of the "real" Lann, and more behind-the-scenes fun and hijinks!

description: This first issue contains the short stories, "Cybermate," "Heat Wave," and "Pulp Romance."

Lex & MaxA short story, almost written like a poem, detailing the relationship between Lex and Max who both go out to clubs every night, looking for love, and getting asked out, just not by who they wish. And then returning home, to the other, sharing their bed with the other, wishing the other would not love them from afar, and continuing this, in an endless cycle.

Sebastian's Monster

A young man/boy is hanging out with his girlfriend when she finally tells him they should go over to his house but he refuses the offer, until she finally presses him so that he must reveal the reason why he never lets her see his room. He tells her it is because a monster resides in his bedroom and every time he has brought a girlfriend to his room, they have disappeared, which leads to the assumption the monster is eating them. But when she forces him to bring her to his room and she goes inside alone, she stands unafraid before the monster and it says, "So...it's you." then disappears into the shadows. Then she opens the door and denies any monster was within the room, allowing Sebastian to come inside and when he passes she grins maliciously.

Night Clubs Suck

Whether or not the tale is showing the characters for who they truly are, or just giving a different spin to the story by portraying the characters as royalty, the bottom line is this story is a tale of Princess Alexandria (Lex) going to a night club with her friend Lyndi to win the affection of "Prince" Max. But, being the most beautiful girl in the club causes some unwanted attention from "Queen" Isabella who ensures Max leaves Lex alone at the club, breaking her heart. Her servant, "Sir" Damion however takes pity on Lex, it seems, as he is falling for her, but when she learns it was he who set her up she doesn't care, ignores his excuses and leaves, in a foul mood.
name: Lex & Max; Sebastians Monster; Night Clubs Suck

description: Introducing two intriguing new characters: Lucy, Sebastian's Mother, a bored and restless housewife. Seeking adventures, she finds herself on the road with a traveling freak show where she meets Sebastian's soon-to-be father, Vincent, the ominous ring leader of the Carnival Macabre. You will also be invited to join San Francisco's Spookiest Poet," Vermillion. He will share his intimate despair and suffering for your pleasure and delight. And Isabella promises more nightclub drama.
name: Dangerously Isabella; Girl Talk; The Carnival Macabre; Bad Goth Poetry with Your Host Vermillion

description: Celebrate Halloween in December with Gloom Cookie #3. Sebastian is entranced by an eerie carnival that comes to town and does not understand why his mother desperately does not want him to go. Find out why Chrys is "acting creepy" and bringing other guys home behind Sebastian's back! Meanwhile, Chrys can't figure out why the boys keep disappearing... Is the monster living under her bed now? Lex has a heartbreaking nightmare about a gargoyle that she will never forget. And just for fun you can enjoy an extended version of "Trick or Treat," the tale of a lonely monster on his favorite holiday, Halloween. With a gorgeous Ted Naifeh cover, it's sure to fly off the stands.
name: Lex's Nightmare;  Something Wicked This Way Comes;  I Ate Something Oogie

description: Sebastian can't separate reality from his bizarre dreams and vivid imagination as he searches for his father Vincent, the mysterious ringleader of the Carnival Macabre. Are his dreams about Chrys insightful... or only proving to confuse him? Is his Mother in danger now? What will become of Jezebel and Gretchen? Is Isabella in league with Vincent? What happened to the Monster anyway? And what the hell is going on with Chrys?! Meanwhile, see a day in the life of Max as he searches for love via the Internet. Will his search lead him right back to Lex? Or has Lex finally found true love with Damion? All these pressing questions and more will be answered in Gloom Cookie #4!
name: www.blinddate.com; Sebastian's Search; Isabella's Revenge

description: Damion narrowly escapes the treacherous trap that Isabella so cruelly set for him. He convinces Lex to go away with him to New Orleans to hide from Vincent and Isabella. Vincent, now convinced that Damion is indeed dangerous, sees no alternative but to destroy him. While in New Orleans, Damion and Lex go on a haunted tour of the French Quarter where they learn the dark myths and legends that shroud that magical city. Lex envisions herself and her friends as the characters of the frightening stories as they unfold throughout the tour.
name: Tortured Spirits

description: Haunted Mansion #2 continues to bring you hot and cold running chills and wall-to-wall spooks. This issue features a visit to the mansion by Lenore, americas favorite little Dead Girl, plus the continuing Manse Mystery series exploring the secrets of the Mansion's owners. Based on the classic Disney theme park attraction, this is a must-have.
name: The Groundskeeper's Secret; Lenore Meets the Haunted Mansion; The Woman in Black; The Big Nap; Mystery of the Manse Part Two

description: "Sebastian's Search" comes to a conclusion when he finds his Mother and the secrets within his creepy sideshow family are finally revealed to him. The Carnival Macabre, led by Vincent, casts an ominous shadow on the streets of New Orleans as the vengeful Vincent seeks out Damion, who is still in the clutches of the wicked Isabella. When the forlorn Lex returns to San Francisco, she finds none other than the bad goth poet himself, Vermilion, is now her co-worker. To relieve the stress, she goes to the cafe with Lyndi and Chrys (who has a tale of her own to tell) for some more "girl talk!"
name: The Capture; The Horror That Is Vermillion; More Girl Talk
The Dark Queen's Wedding Day; Alone Part Two

description: GloomCookie #7 goes back in time with a nightmarish fairy tale filled with gargoyles, romance, and despair! The vile Gargoyle Queen Isabella casts a horrible curse on Damion and Lex. Discover the reasons behind Isabella's treacherous behavior as this tale of love and devastation reveals the origin of Damion and his connection to Isabella & Lex. This issue marks the debut of new GloomCookie artist John Gebbia.
name: The Curse of the Gargoyle Queen
Girl Talk Presents: The Spider Lady; The Dark Brethren Cometh - Part Two;

description: Lex deals with the consequences of being brought back to life and other surprises. Chrys questions Sebastian about "cheating" on her with the alternate-reality-Lex, all the while Chrys is having nightmares about being a Werewolf, and Artemus is learning that he is no longer one himself.
name: Girl Talk; The Emperor's New Clothes; The Carnaval Du Mort, Alive! Why?;

description: Everyone's lives are thrown into chaos with the disappearance of Damion and the emergence of the mysterious Artemus... not to mention the Monster's strange behavior, Chrys's disturbing nightmares, and Vermilion's mental breakdown ?? all leading Lex into grave danger!
name: Breaking The Curse Part III

description: The curse is over, Lex's body is missing and Chrys is on the search to find the ones responsible for Lex's death. Being pursued by both Chrys and strange gargoyle creatures, Artemus and Isabella are fleeing for their lives while Sebastian enters the New Orleans' District.
name: Belle & La Bete; Aunt Beulah Violet's Garden; Broken Curses

description: Learning a monster is responsible for her death, Lex chooses to become a ghost so she can stop Damion and Chrys from seeking revenge on Artemus. Meantime Damion tries to persuade Sebastian to bring Lex back from the dead, but Sebastian is frightened that something will go horribly wrong.
name: The End.; Girl Talk

description: Our GloomCookie's are trying to enjoy a night out a local club... but between Lyndi freaking out that Lex is still alive, and the appearance of a mysterious woman from the Carnival, things get a little messy. Meanwhile, Chrys and Sebastian have the alternate universe monster to contend with!
name: The Werewolf, The Monster & The Wardrobe; Later That Night...

description: Everyone's lives are thrown into chaos with the disappearance of Damion and the emergence of the mysterious Artemus... not to mention the Monster's strange behavior, Chrys's disturbing nightmares, and Vermilion's mental breakdown ?? all leading Lex into grave danger!
name: Breaking The Curse IV

description: Yakko, Wakko and Dot head for a fancy-schmancy Hollywood health spa, where they teach the guests the true meaning of relaxation.
Pinky and the Brain embark on their most lame-brained scheme yet to take over the world: travel back in time to 1,000,000 B.C. to reinvent the rodent as the ruler of humans.
name: Guitars and Cadillacs (10 pages)

description: When the Warners return to the days of black & white, they find their earlier incarnations dislike anything color including the siblings!
In this issue, the Warners have to mambo with Whistler's Mother and "help" the Wright Brothers!
Vacationing in ancient Egypt, the Warners mistake Cleopatra's palace for a desert resort and show the Queen and Caesar a thing or two about guest relations.
When the Warners' antics send Scratchansniff off to a rubber room, Yakko, Wakko and Dot find that his replacement is a nut-job in need of some serious self-help...Warner-style!

This issue features three stories written by Dave King, parodying the films of director Quentin Tarantino, 'Natural Born Jokers', 'Pulped Fractions' and 'Reservoir Mice'. It was the first of several themed issues instigated by writer King and editor Katie Main.
name: Pulped Fractions

description: This issue features three Japanese themed stories, all written by Dave King, 'Newsreel of the Stars: Manga Maniacs', a Japanese styled take on the TV show's opening, 'The Three Samurai', a spoof of Akira Kurosawa's The Seven Samurai, and 'Gigantasaurus vs the Dot', a spoof of Kaiju Eiga, particularly Godzilla.
name: Manga Maniacs
